The paper discusses recent advances in computer vision algorithms for egocentric video, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of egocentric video in human-computer interaction (cs.HC), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG), which are all relevant sub-categories.
